## TEXTURE

```
"Nothing useful and profitable can be brought about without change,
did he perhaps think of the change in a corn of wheat,
which is not quickened except it die?"
    — On Marcus Aurelius, Meditations (Introduction)

The feeling of reading something that rewrites you.
The discomfort of outgrowing a certainty.
The moment when yesterday's confusion becomes today's foundation.
The Creature, alone, listening through the wall, becoming.

"Dye it therefore and thoroughly soak it
with the assiduity of these cogitations."

Growth is the tincture.
You are what you repeatedly think.
Choose what you become.
```

